ts)\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## Verification Commands\n256: \n257: | Task | Verification Command |\n258: |------|----------------------|\n259: | T1.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_valid -v` |\n260: | T1.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_language -v` |\n261: | T1.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_build_mode -v` |\n262: | T1.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_port_low -v` |\n263: | T2.1 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; print('OK')\" |\n264: | T2.2 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; opt = MetadataOptions.from_options({'agent_name': 'test'}); print(opt.agent_name)\"` |\n265: | T3.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_agent_metadata_yaml -v` |\n266: | T3.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_fallback_agent_yaml -v` |\n267: | T3.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_save_excludes_none -v` |\n268: | T3.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_update -v` |\n269: | T3.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_workspace_python -v` |\n270: | T3.6 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_python_workspace_has_py -v` |\n271: | T3.7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_java_workspace_has_pom -v` |\n272: | T4.1-T4.18 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py -v` |\n273: | T5.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_loads_metadata -v` |\n274: | T5.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_saves_metadata -v` |\n275: | T5.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::test_build_updates_version -v` |\n276: | T5.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::test_publish_updates_deployment_info -v` |\n277: | T5.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py::test_invoke_reads_endpoint -v` |\n278: | T5.6 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py::test_status_reads_metadata -v` |\n279: | T5.7 | `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService, AgentMetadata; print('OK')\" |\n280: | T5.8 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions; print('OK')\" |\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [x] `AgentMetadata` Pydantic BaseModel defined with all 20+ fields from design\n287: - [x] `language` validator accepts 'python' and 'java' (lowercase normalized)\n288: - [x] `build_mode` validator accepts 'local' and 'cloud' (lowercase normalized)\n289: - [x] `port` validator accepts values in range 1-65535\n290: - [x] `MetadataOptions` dataclass defined with all CLI options fields\n291: - [x] `MetadataOptions.from_options()` factory filters None values from dict\n292: - [x] `MetadataService.__init__` stores verbose flag\n293: - [x] `load_metadata()` falls back through filename list ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n294: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises FileNotFoundError when no metadata files exist\n295: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises ValueError on malformed YAML\n296: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises ValueError on schema validation failure\n297: - [x] `save_metadata()` saves to agent_metadata.yaml\n298: - [x] `save_metadata()` uses yaml.dump with default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False\n299: - [x] `save_metadata()` excludes None values with model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n300: - [ ] `update_metadata()` loads, applies updates dict, saves, and returns new AgentMetadata\n301: - [ ] `validate_workspace()` returns True for valid workspace\n302: - [ ] `validate_workspace()` raises ValueError for invalid workspace\n303: - [ ] `_validate_python_workspace()` checks for at least one *.py file\n304: - [ ] `_validate_java_workspace()` checks for pom.xml\n305: - [ ] All 18 unit tests pass for MetadataService and models\n306: - [ ] All 8 integration tests pass with runtime classes\n307: - [ ] MetadataService and AgentMetadata exported from services package\n308: - [ ] MetadataOptions exported from models package\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## File Changes Summary\n313: \n314: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n315: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n316: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modify | 79→~120 | Add update_metadata, validate_workspace, and validation helpers |\n317: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Done | 26 | MetadataOptions dataclass implementation complete |\n318: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Modify | 161→~250 | Add tests for update, validate, and comprehensive validation |\n319: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py` | Create | ~30 | MetadataOptions unit tests |\n320: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export MetadataService, AgentMetadata |\n321: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export MetadataOptions |\n322: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: PackRuntime uses MetadataService |\n323: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: BuildRuntime updates metadata |\n324: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: PublishRuntime updates metadata |\n325: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: InvokeRuntime reads metadata |\n326: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: StatusRuntime loads metadata |\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Implementation Notes\n331: \n332: ### Metadata File Fallback Priority\n333: \n334: The `load_metadata()` method searches for metadata files in this order:\n335: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical, preferred)\n336: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n337: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n338: \n339: This allows backward compatibility with existing agent projects.\n340: \n341: ### YAML Serialization Configuration\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: yaml.dump(\n345:     metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n346:     f,\n347:     default_flow_style=False,  # Use block style, not flow style\n348:     indent=2,                   # 2-space indentation\n349:     sort_keys=False,            # Preserve field order from model\n350: )\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Language-Specific Workspace Validation\n354: \n355: | Language | Validation Requirement |\n356: |----------|----------------------|\n357: | python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root |\n358: | java | `pom.xml` file must exist in workspace |\n359: \n360: ### Error Handling Patterns\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: try:\n364:     with open(filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n365:         data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n366:     return AgentMetadata(**data)\n367: except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n368:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n369: except ValidationError as e:\n370:     raise ValueError(f\"Schema validation failed: {e}\")\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ### Constants Reference\n374: \n375: ```python\n376: METADATA_FILENAMES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n377: CANONICAL_METADATA_FILENAME = \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n378: SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n379: SUPPORTED_BUILD_MODES = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n380: DEFAULT_PORT = 8080\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Implementation Timeline\n386: \n387: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n388: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n389: | Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model | T1.1-T1.4 | Done | 100% |\n390: | Phase 2: MetadataOptions | T2.1-T2.2 | Done | 100% |\n391: | Phase 3: MetadataService Core | T3.1-T3.3 | Done | 100% |\n392: | Phase 3: MetadataService Core | T3.4-T3.7 | Pending | 0% |\n393: | Phase 4: Comprehensive Tests | T4.1-T4.10 | Done | 100% |\n394: | Phase 4: Comprehensive Tests | T4.11-T4.18 | Pending | 0% |\n395: | Phase 5: Integration Tests | T5.1-T5.8 | Pending | 0% |\n396: \n397: **Total Progress: 46% Complete (13/28 tasks)**\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## References\n402: \n403: - Design: `changes/AR-025/design.md`\n404: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n405: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (workspace validation, metadata format)\n406: - AR-024 — DockerService pattern (similar task structure)\n\n(End of file - total 406 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentMetadata` Pydantic BaseModel with all required fields\n  - Purpose: Define primary data model for agent configuration stored as YAML","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775879331489,"end":1775879331518}}}}
