{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879339843,"sessionID":"ses_285582da9ffeVekszX7tvUptvr","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa83f2c001ZXnqUUvn1qZoh7","messageID":"msg_d7aa81f14001pXX5Qr6Yf833U2","sessionID":"ses_285582da9ffeVekszX7tvUptvr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8b300d98a1a84cfebf365c863a8dbfb1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n18: \n19: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n24: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n25: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n30: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n31: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n36: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n42: \n43: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n48: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n49: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n54: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n55: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n60: \n61: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Create session\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n66: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n67: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Delete session\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n72: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n73: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n78: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n79: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n84: \n85: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Execute command\n88: \n89: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n90: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Files API — write file\n93: \n94: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Files API — upload file\n98: \n99: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Session header management\n105: \n106: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n111: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n112: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n117: \n118: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Command failure\n121: \n122: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n123: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n129: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n130: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n135: \n136: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n141: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n142: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Data Structures\n147: \n148: | Class | Fields | Purpose |\n149: |-------|--------|---------|\n150: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client` | Main client for code interpreter sessions |\n151: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url`, `session`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout` | HTTP client for Workload Manager |\n152: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `session_id`, `base_url`, `session`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout` | HTTP client for Router data plane |\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## API Contracts\n157: \n158: ### Control Plane — HTTP\n159: \n160: | Method | Path | Notes |\n161: |--------|------|-------|\n162: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n163: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n164: \n165: ### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) — HTTP\n166: \n167: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n168: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n169: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n170: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n171: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n172: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n173: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ## Dependencies\n178: \n179: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n180: |---------|---------|---------|\n181: | `requests` | — | HTTP client with connection pooling |\n182: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT handling |\n183: | `cryptography` | — | Cryptographic operations |\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## File Structure\n188: \n189: | Path | Purpose |\n190: |------|---------|\n191: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports: `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n192: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` class |\n193: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n194: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n195: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n196: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n197: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` helper |\n198: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` helper |\n199: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` helper |\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## Validation Checklist\n204: \n205: - [ ] `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` with `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, `session_id`\n206: - [ ] Router URL required: raises `ValueError` if missing via arg and env\n207: - [ ] Context manager: `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `stop()`\n208: - [ ] Session reuse: skips `create_session` when `session_id` provided\n209: - [ ] Data plane init failure cleanup: deletes session, logs warning, re-raises\n210: - [ ] `execute_command`: JSON body `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`, read timeout buffer `+2.0`\n211: - [ ] Non-zero exit: raises `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`\n212: - [ ] `run_code`: writes timestamped `.py` file, executes via `python3`\n213: - [ ] `write_file`: base64 content, mode `\"0644\"`\n214: - [ ] `upload_file`: multipart POST with `x-agentcube-session-id`\n215: - [ ] `download_file`: GET with `stream=True`\n216: - [ ] `list_files`: GET with query `path`\n217: - [ ] Session header: `x-agentcube-session-id` on all data plane requests\n218: - [ ] Control plane: `POST` `/v1/code-interpreter`, `DELETE` `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`\n219: - [ ] `delete_session`: 404 returns `True`, other failures log and return `False`\n220: - [ ] Auth token: explicit arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n221: - [ ] `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header when token present\n222: - [ ] Default timeouts: read `120s`, connect `5.0s`\n223: - [ ] Exception hierarchy: `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## References\n228: \n229: - `python-sdk/design.md` — AgentCube Python SDK design\n230: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentCube Python SDK specification\n\n(End of file - total 230 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879339830,"end":1775879339841}}}}
